[SN]TITLE[SN]
West Belfast: Man charged after health centre attack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 34-year-old man has been charged after windows were smashed and a doctor was verbally abused at a west Belfast health centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened on the Whiterock Road at about 15:00 GMT on Friday afternoon.
Police said it was witnessed by people waiting to pick up prescriptions, including children.
The man has been charged with two counts of criminal damage, disorderly behaviour and of assault on police.
He is due to appear at Belfast Magistrates Court on 5 December.
